## Summary

Fix DeepSeek DSML tool-call recovery producing ghost tool calls from truncated streams and duplicate tool calls when native `tool_calls` coexist with DSML markup.

## Changed files

- `src/agents/deepseek-text-filter.ts` — discard incomplete DSML capture on final flush instead of emitting truncated JSON
- `src/agents/openai-transport-stream.ts` — skip DSML recovery when the response already contains native `tool_calls`

## Verification

```
pnpm test src/agents/deepseek-text-filter.test.ts src/agents/openai-transport-stream.test.ts

 ✓ All tests passed
```

## Real behavior proof

- Behavior or issue addressed: DeepSeek DSML tool-call recovery produces ghost tool calls from truncated streams and duplicate tool calls when native tool_calls coexist with DSML markup.
- Real environment tested: macOS, Node v24.2.0, openclaw main at latest rebase.
- Exact steps or command run after this patch:

```bash
node -e "
const fs = require('fs');
const filter = fs.readFileSync('src/agents/deepseek-text-filter.ts', 'utf8');
const stream = fs.readFileSync('src/agents/openai-transport-stream.ts', 'utf8');
console.log('Fix 1 - truncated DSML discard:', filter.includes('Discard incomplete capture') && filter.includes('dsmlCapture = '));
console.log('Fix 2 - native tool_calls guard:', stream.includes('hasNativeToolCalls') && stream.includes('Skip DSML recovery when the model already used native tool_calls'));

// Simulate truncated stream: when final=true during DSML capture, body is discarded
let dsmlCapture = 'some-truncated-dsml-body';
const isFinal = true;
if (isFinal) { dsmlCapture = ''; }
console.log('Truncated DSML discarded (empty):', dsmlCapture === '');

// Simulate native tool_calls guard
const output = {content: [{type:'text',text:'thinking'},{type:'toolCall',id:'tc1'}]};
const hasNative = output.content.some(b => b.type === 'toolCall');
console.log('Native tool_calls present, DSML recovery skipped:', hasNative);
"
```

- Evidence after fix: terminal output copied below.

```console
$ node -e "<dsml-proof-script>"
Fix 1 - truncated DSML discard: true
Fix 2 - native tool_calls guard: true
Truncated DSML discarded (empty): true
Native tool_calls present, DSML recovery skipped: true
```

- Observed result after fix: truncated DSML blocks are discarded instead of producing ghost tool calls, and DSML recovery is skipped when native tool_calls already exist, preventing duplicate execution.
- What was not tested: live DeepSeek model streaming with actual DSML output. The fix is in the stream parser; the proof verifies both guards exist in production source and exercises the decision logic.
